						               													<description>Card game similar to Touring was published in a form fitting box with 75 cards:  39 mileage, 10 take off, 10 weather, 15 hazards and 1 Lucky Lindy.  Based on the historic flight of the same year, hazards include forced landing, storm,  fog, engine trouble, etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Inventor was a flier in the US Navy and also made gliders and models.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Came out in the same year as the similar game Lindy, the New Flying Game by Parker Bros., apparently the subject of a lawsuit by Nucraft against Parker Bros which the latter won. This caused the Nucraft game to have a far more limited production and thus their game is far more valuable to collectors today. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Not so sure about this interpretation. A note on the rules for&amp;#10;     Nucraft's game Crash game indicate that Parker Brothers bought&amp;#10;     the rights to the Lindy game from Nucraft. So it would seem&amp;#10;     that Parker bought out Nucraft and shelved their version of&amp;#10;     the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the lawsuit Nucraft issued a different game called Crash, The New Airplane Game. It seems to be a Parcheesi type game played with three planes per color and a four color spinner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Nucraft Toys ended in 1933 when the company started operating under the name of its founder Paul K. Guillow.  The company Paul K. Guillow did not produce any games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
